Aspect Model Claim Data

urn:samm:io.catenax.fleet.claim_data:3.0.0#ClaimData
For Catena-X(CX) business case Quality Management. Supported technical features: delta update feature, meta information feature and additionalInformationList key-value pairs. The supported model features are described in detail in the Catena-X Quality KIT. This model is used to exchange claim information. FleetClaim data model is used to exchange a list of claims. A Claim is a complaint of a vehicle owner. The assumption for this data model is that a customer is coming to a repair shop and complaining about a malfunction in his/her vehicle during vehicle's warranty period. The repair shop than diagnosis the car (this is the link to FleetDiagnostic data model) and can eventually exchange faulty parts. The repair shop later hands in the invoice to the OEM to compensate his work. Defining the uniqueness of a claim: A claim gets a unique claimId (unique within one OEM). A claim is related to one vehicle that can be identified by anonymizedVIN and refers to a potentially faulty part/component in the vehicle. A claim is coming from a specific country - this is normally the country of the repair shop. A claim can contain a list of replaced parts that were put out of the affected vehicle and a list of spare parts/new parts that were put into the affected vehicle. Some of the old, potentially faulty parts are send back to the part's manufacturer for detailed analyses (this is the link to the PartsAnalyses data model).

Claim

A claim is when a customer has a problem with his vehicle and goes to the workshop to get this problem fixed. Sometimes potentially faulty parts are exchanged.

Optional

In payload
Yes
Payload key
repairDate
Constraints
  • Date Regular Expression Nullable
    Description
    This regular expressions enforces a given date according ISO 8601 local date. General format is YYYY-MM-DD. YYYY can be 0000..9999. MM-DD is checked together: months 01,03,05,07,08,10,12 must have DD in the range of 01..31 days, months 04,06,09,11 must have DD in the range of 01..30 days, month 02 must have DD in the range of 01..29 days.
    Regular expression
    ^([0-9]{4})-(((0[1,3,5,7,8]|1[0,2])-((0[1-9])|([1,2][0-9])|(3[0,1])))|((0[4,6,9]|11)-((0[1-9])|([1,2][0-9])|(30)))|((02)-((0[1-9])|([1,2][0-9]))))$|^null$|^NULL$

Record status

The record operation enumeration can be used to realize delta update concept. An example using scenario that data delivery runs weekly: Week0: All data is transferred -> all rows have recordStatus=new. Week1: Only the changed data is transferred: That means new rows, or updated or deleted rows: New rows get recordStatus=new, changed rows get recordStatus=changed and deleted/removed rows get recordStatus=deleted.
Name
recordStatus
Characteristic
Enumeration
Values
  • new
  • updated
  • deleted
  • same
Type http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string
Example
updated
Optional
Yes
In payload
Yes
Payload key
recordStatus

Part identifier

A unique part identifier in this data-space. Property is optional as of now not all parts have this identifier.
Name
partId
Characteristic
Trait
Reference
  • https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4122
Type http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string
Example
urn:uuid:580d3adf-1981-44a0-a214-13d6ceed9000
Optional
Yes
In payload
Yes
Payload key
partId
Constraints
  • UUID v4 Regular Expression
    Description
    The provided regular expression ensures that the UUID is composed of five groups of characters separated by hyphens, in the form 8-4-4-4-12 for a total of 36 characters (32 hexadecimal characters and 4 hyphens), optionally prefixed by "urn:uuid:" to make it an IRI.
    Reference
    • https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc4122
    Regular expression
    (^[0-9a-fA-F]{8}-[0-9a-fA-F]{4}-[0-9a-fA-F]{4}-[0-9a-fA-F]{4}-[0-9a-fA-F]{12}$)|(^urn:uuid:[0-9a-fA-F]{8}-[0-9a-fA-F]{4}-[0-9a-fA-F]{4}-[0-9a-fA-F]{4}-[0-9a-fA-F]{12}$)
Data matrix code

String that is encoded in a data matrix code. Data matrix codes or short DMC are labelled/printed on parts. Example: A data matrix code can combine supplier name, part type, manufacturing and many more information. A DMC string is often unique within this data provider.
